COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1250, L.D. 1879
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment provides for the apportionment of the tax proposed in the bill. The
55 amendment restructures the cascade of funds in the bill to 4 funds and specifies that each
66 priority must be fully funded before proceeding to the next priority. The amendment
77 removes the exemption from property tax for agricultural buildings as proposed in the bill.
88 The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
99 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
